48
0:02:28.997,000 --> 0:02:31,000
to create better lives and futures for themselves

49
0:02:32.346,000 --> 0:02:33,000
after they serve their time.

50
0:02:34.931,000 --> 0:02:37,000
This piece is entitled, "Where I Live."

51
0:02:40.218,000 --> 0:02:43,000
I live in a world where most people are too afraid to go.

52
0:02:44.441,000 --> 0:02:46,000
Surrounded by tall, concrete walls,

53
0:02:46.801,000 --> 0:02:47,000
steel bars,

54
0:02:47.976,000 --> 0:02:48,000
where razor wire have a way

55
0:02:49.294,000 --> 0:02:52,000
of cutting away at the hopes for a brighter tomorrow.

56
0:02:53.697,000 --> 0:02:54,000
I live in a world

57
0:02:54.872,000 --> 0:02:55,000
that kill people who kill people

58
0:02:56.429,000 --> 0:02:57,000
in order to teach people

59
0:02:57.604,000 --> 0:02:58,000
that killing people is wrong.

60
0:03:00.285,000 --> 0:03:01,000
Imagine that.

61
0:03:02.111,000 --> 0:03:03,000
Better yet,

62
0:03:03.286,000 --> 0:03:06,000
